# Project Roadmap

## Short‑Term (Version 0.1)
- Publish repo with manifesto, FAQ, and roadmap.  
- Attract contributors to explore overlay engines (FFmpeg, VLC, NodeCG).  
- Begin drafting cue file formats and UX mockups.  
- Seed discussions in developer forums and family communities.

## Medium‑Term (Version 0.2–0.5)
- Build simple cue editors and GUI tools for families.  
- Cross‑platform support (Windows, Mac, Linux).  
- Community guidelines for lawful collaboration.  
- Publish technical + legal white paper documenting resilience against hostile litigation practices.  
- Share concept diagrams to visualize overlay architecture.

## Long‑Term (Version 1.0+)
- Normalize overlays as a standard playback feature, like captions.  
- Mass adoption by families and communities.  
- Encourage co‑option by platforms into official “family modes.”  
- Advocacy for broader recognition of lawful personal playback rights.  
- Ensure resilience against hostile litigation by decentralizing tools and community ownership.
